author: {'steamid': '76561198098342214', 'num_games_owned': 10629, 'num_reviews': 595, 'playtime_forever': 750, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 206, 'playtime_at_review': 750, 'last_played': 1711414011}
review:
[h1]Rick and Morty: Virtual Rick-ality[/h1]

Esse jogo é praticamente um episódio mesmo da série, mas no geral ele é bem curto, se você não ficar meio perdido em alguma parte do jogo você provavelmente deve terminar a história em questão de um pouco mais de 2 horas. No meu caso levei só um pouco mais que isso, pois o problema é que o jogo está em inglês e embora eu entenda bem, são muitas dicas que o Rick e o Morty vão passando durante sua jogatina e as vezes pelo menos não consegui manjar sobre o que eu tinha que fazer, então se acontecer contigo o ideal é assistir um vídeo de alguém jogando e pegar um spoilerzinho mesmo do que ficar preso, mas provavelmente vc talvez não vai precisar ate pq eu sou meio tapado tbm pra esse tipo de jogo kkkkk

Agora dá pra estender além dessas horas bastante indo atrás das conquistas e descobrindo os segredos do jogo, a maioria delas é de boa, só tem umas 2 conquistas que vc pode demorar um pouco e são difíceis, mas não impossíveis seguindo algumas dicas, eu acabei me animando com o game e consegui pegar tudo, por isso estou recomendado.

[b]Recomendo, mas lembrando que é um jogo de realidade virtual então somente jogadores com RV podem jogar, mas eu fiquei sabendo recentemente que os jogos da Adult Swim vão ser removido e parece que esse também será, então é complicado recomendar pra quem deseja ter esse jogo mas não tem certeza se irá ter um RV algum dia. Recomendo pensar muito pois é um jogo bom e eu gostei bastante, mas já era em breve esse irá ser removido de vendas, praticamente certo que vai ser, então quem tiver interesse tem que comprar o mais rápido possível.[/b]

author: {'steamid': '76561198131417118', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 18, 'playtime_forever': 270, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 270, 'playtime_at_review': 270, 'last_played': 1711362043}

Also das Spiel an sich ist sehr gut gelungen. 
Die Ideen sind halt echt stark und es macht einfach tierisch viel Spaß.

Aber für den Preis finde ich geht das nicht.

Für mich wären 10€ dafür als kleine Unterhaltung gerechtfertigt gewesen.
Schade, wirklich. Dennoch, wem die Spiellänge und der Preis nichts ausmachen, wird sehr viel Spaß damit haben.

author: {'steamid': '76561197961214315', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 22, 'playtime_forever': 46, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 46, 'last_played': 1704618513}
review:
It is a VR Chores Simulator where you find the thing, combine the thing, make the thing, and insert the thing; most VR titles in this realm are basically the same so the writing and flavor spin on it is important.

If you like early season Rick and Morty (remember this game is fairly aged at this point) you will enjoy this. It has enough nods to the show to make it fun to look around and do random things that will get the characters to talk to you. The premise is good enough to be engaging, all while being a bit snarky at you like you would expect from Rick as you're a Morty but not even a full Morty.

With it's length and how there isn't a ton to do in the game though I'd say this is a recommendation on sale, not at full price at all.

review:
El juego no se inicia a menos que use esta solución muy difícil de encontrar, es un buen juego, pero los nuevos jugadores tengan cuidado.

PROBLEMA DE LANZAMIENTO RESUELTO
Si tiene una CPU Intel de décima generación o más nueva, siga los pasos a continuación para solucionarlo:

Haz clic derecho en el juego>Propiedades>General>Opciones de inicio

Tipo:

cmd /c "set OPENSSL_ia32cap=~0x200000200000000 && %command%"

en el cuadro disponible y debería iniciarse.
!ENCONTRÉ ESTO Y FUNCIONÓ ¡ESPERO QUE TENGAN SUS NOTIFICACIONES ACTIVADAS PARA ESTA COSA!

author: {'steamid': '76561198028867777', 'num_games_owned': 616, 'num_reviews': 4, 'playtime_forever': 180, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 180, 'last_played': 1704536026}
review:
Great short little game. Highly recommended to purchase this game if it is on sale or if you're a Rick and Morty Fan. The game is only about 2 hours long with not much replayability other than trophy completion.

[b]HOW TO FIX WHITE SCREEN/ BLACK SCREEN/ GAME LOADING ISSUES: [/b]
The problem is that you're not meant to launch this game via the Steam Client, but instead use the SteamVR and load that game within the SteamVR application. If you load the game directly via your steam library you may experience a WHITE SCREEN/ BLACK SCREEN/ GAME LOADING ISSUE.

[b]HOW TO RESOLVE THIS ISSUE?[/b]
- [b]STEP 1: [/b]Connect your device via the LinkCable (or Type-C if your computer has a type-C port) (Both work fine).
- [b]STEP 2: [/b]Allow the device (your laptop) access to connect to your VR Headset - Select "Allow".
- [b]STEP 3: [/b]Enable the Quest Link via your VR Headset - Select "Enable".
- [b]STEP 4: [/b]Launch the SteamVR Application and select the Rick and Morty: Virtual Rick-ality from your Steam Library.

Hopefully that helps others that may experience that issues.

author: {'steamid': '76561198980930444', 'num_games_owned': 1128, 'num_reviews': 99, 'playtime_forever': 1353, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 485, 'last_played': 1710032222}
review:
The Rick and Morty VR game is simply stunning! She completely conveys the atmosphere of this crazy and unpredictable animated series. As one wise man said: "The more Rick Sanchez exists in the world, the better and more beautiful life becomes!" Playing this game is to jump right into the world of Rick and Morty, become part of their crazy adventures and experience the real magic of reality.

As a big fan of Rick and Morty, I can't help but recommend this game to all fans of the animated series. Its gameplay is as close as possible to the original style of the series, and the details and dialogues of the characters are made with such love and attention that they simply cannot leave anyone indifferent.

Of course, after completing the game, it will be a long time to wait for the new season of the series, but this game will be the perfect way to take time and quench the thirst for new adventures of Rick and Morty. The Rick and Morty VR game is a real masterpiece that every fan of the series should try. She perfectly conveys all the humor, sarcasm and madness that we loved so much in the animated series.

Jump into the portal and travel to amazing worlds, experience for yourself that wonderful combination of science fiction and black humor that makes Rick and Morty so unique. The Rick and Morty VR game is a real godsend for all fans of the series. Don't miss the opportunity to plunge into the world of endless adventures and laughter!

author: {'steamid': '76561198069052016', 'num_games_owned': 113, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 37, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 37, 'last_played': 1703896510}
review:
Game Wouldn't Launch Unless i used this very hard to find fix, its a good game but new players be careful 

LAUNCH ISSUE RESOLVED
If you have an intel 10th gen or newer CPU follow the steps below to fix:

Right click game>Properties>General>Launch Options

Type:

cmd /c "set OPENSSL_ia32cap=~0x200000200000000 && %command%"

into available box, and it should launch!
!I FOUND THIS AND IT WORKED I HOPE YALL HAVE YOUR NOTIFICATIONS ON FOR THIS THING!

author: {'steamid': '76561197999403507', 'num_games_owned': 1175, 'num_reviews': 1276, 'playtime_forever': 19, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 19, 'last_played': 1703601042}
review:
Lubisz Rick'a i Morty'ego? Super. To ten tytuł jest tylko popłuczynami. Nuda, nuda, nuda, słabizna i brak słów, no i nuda.
Bardzo marny i przede wszystkim nudny tytuł. Można było na wiele innych sposobów oddać gameplayowo klimat i żeby było zabawnie. A wyszło zupełnie płytko i beznamiętnie.
Poza znalezieniem się w garażu Ricka i możliwościami interakcji z przedmiotami, nie ma tu większego funu.
Kupowałem ten tytuł napalony jak szczerbaty na suchary, licząc, że będzie to świetna zabawa VR. 
Po kilkunastu minutach rozgrywki stwierdzam że to pan kupka z pupki, A Rick and Morty miał marketingowo unieść ten tytuł. Żadna franczyza nie uniesie niestety takiego nudnego gameplayu.
Szkoda na to pieniędzy i czasu. Dobrze, że można to zwrócić. 

Aaa i zapomniałem dodać, że gra ma zwalone punkty teleportacji, a raczej poważny ich brak, bo rozgrywka dedykowana jest chyba do gry w jakiejś dużej sali a nie salonie czy pokoju. Jedyny sposób interakcji z przedmiotami, to podejście do nich, a na to braknie miejsca w pokoju bo swobodnej teleportacji i ruchu brak w tej grze.

review: This title is a fantastic little adventure. The teleport controls are slightly annoying, but that can be solved pretty easily if you have a huge open space to play in and can manage actually walking around instead. Rick’s garage is full of whimsical devices and gadgets. As you can imagine, loads of references to the show. While it does have a story line that you can easily prioritize, it also at times acts like a sand box game where you are free to tinker and mess around in Rick’s garage. The absurdity of the tasks you will have to figure out are sometimes pretty tricky. The fully charged achievement in this game was so difficult to beat that it is actually the rarest achievement I've earned. It is a task so absurd that is actually 9 times harder than the PlayStation VR version of the game.

review: I noticed when looking through the reviews of other people a lot of people had issues running this game but I didn't, it ran perfectly for me and I somewhat enjoyed it. But I don't recommend it, and I'll explain why. I bought this game initially because I love Rick and Morty so when I saw a VR game for it I was excited and really wanted to try it out. However, this game really lacks a story and any content. It's really just you sitting in a room only being able to jump around to a couple of spots and pick up and interact with a few objects, this game really lacks in anything that'll keep you interested for more than 20 minutes, and it's not cheap. I do not think this game is worth the money that you have to spend in order to purchase it, and I do not think it's worth your time, because it really isn't fun.

author: {'steamid': '76561198396669980', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 13, 'playtime_forever': 18, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 18, 'last_played': 1699878829}
review:
Ich kann das Spiel in keinem Fall weiterempfehlen, außer ihr habt eine leere Lagerhalle als Platz um VR zu spielen.

Die Bewegung innerhalb des Spiels ist an eure Bewegung im realen Raum gebunden. Eine Bewegung über Thumbsticks oder Button ist nicht möglich.
Ich habe 2,5 X 2,0 m VR-Fläche und bin ständig an Regale und Wände gestoßen, wenn ich versucht habe Tätigkeiten in diesem Spiel auszuführen.
Finde es sehr schade, da ich das Spiel sehr gerne gespielt hätte, da ich ein "Rick & Morty"-Fan bin und den Comic-Stiel echt mag.

Fazit:
Grafik, Ton, Spielprinzip = Top
Steuerung = unspielbar

author: {'steamid': '76561199443370423', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 238, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 238, 'last_played': 1693095658}
review: I was looking forward to playing this game, and it was fun when i started, but the amount of content and the replayability is very bad. The game can be finished in under an hour and there is nothing to do once it is finished. I finished the game in about two hours and over half of that was just messing around with a few features and letting my friends play. Overall, the game is kind of fun at first, but definitely not worth the money at all. Even if it was $5 it would not be worth it. P.S. the movement is all roomscale and there is no turning with your controller, so you need quite a large playspace to enjoy this game at all.

author: {'steamid': '76561199088911994', 'num_games_owned': 197, 'num_reviews': 43, 'playtime_forever': 217, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 217, 'last_played': 1679858095}
review:
[b] ONLY GET IF ON SALE! NOT WORTH $20!!! [/b]

The game is fun, and if you are a fan of Rick and Morty, then you'll get lots of giggles from this game. It's immersive, detailed, and does reference the show lots of times.

The only thing that sucks about this game is how short it is. 2-3 hours is all it takes for you to do everything in the game. Like, literally every feature, including achievement hunting (other than the really hard achievements). Because of this, the game is not worth $20 AT ALL. I would ONLY get this game on sale, and on sale only. The VR settings are also outdated I believe, as it is missing a lot of calibration settings that could mess with how you play. So get a big area ready, you are gonna need it.

review:
Fun, short, funny rick and morty experience. There's tons and tons of dialogue everywhere, and you like hearing Justin Roiland ramble to himself for hours, buy this game. It's quite expensive for its short runtime in my opinion, and it won't take you too long to 100% it. The battery minigame was really fun and difficult. This was a really fun game to just mess around with, as well. You can play Troy for ages and mess with the combination machine to make all different kinds of objects.

very good VR title, nothing too special.

author: {'steamid': '76561198273211342', 'num_games_owned': 112, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 28, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 28, 'last_played': 1689690730}
review: I'm not a fan of VR games that restrict your movement and don't allow you to turn with the controller. Its really annoying when using in a smaller play space and I wish they'd put more effort into making it easier to move around and just experience the world of Rick and Morty in VR. You have to teleport which is super restrictive. It feels almost intentional like they're giving you a big middle finger for giving them money and expecting to be able to explore what they've created. I'm glad I at least got it on sale.
